abstract: Following is a transcript of the fourth and final day of confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, as recorded by Federal News Service.
snippet: Following is a transcript of the fourth and final day of confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, as recorded by Federal News Service.
lead_paragraph: Following is a transcript of the fourth and final day of confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, as recorded by Federal News Service. Judge Sotomayor answered second-round questions from Senators Jon Kyl, Dianne Feinstein, Lindsey Graham, Amy Klobuchar, John Cornyn, Arlen Specter, Tom Coburn, and Al Franken. A final round of questions were asked by Senators Jeff Sessions, Orrin G. Hatch, Charles E. Grassley, Kyl, Graham, Cornyn and Coburn.

abstract: The confirmation hearings of Judge Sonia Sotomayor began in the middle of the second round of questioning by the senators on the Judiciary committee.
snippet: The confirmation hearings of Judge Sonia Sotomayor began in the middle of the second round of questioning by the senators on the Judiciary committee.
lead_paragraph: It's a Wrap | 8:52 p.m. The Senate Judiciary Committee has concluded the confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, going well into the evening with many witnesses testifying for and against her positions.

abstract: Stay with us for updates throughout the day at the Senate Judiciary Committee hearings for Judge Sotomayor.
snippet: Stay with us for updates throughout the day at the Senate Judiciary Committee hearings for Judge Sotomayor.
lead_paragraph: It’s a Wrap | 8:52 p.m.  The Senate Judiciary Committee has concluded the confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, going well into the evening with many witnesses testifying for and against her positions.

abstract: Following is a transcript of the third day of confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, as recorded by Federal News Service.
snippet: Following is a transcript of the third day of confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, as recorded by Federal News Service.
lead_paragraph: Following is a transcript of the third day of confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor, as recorded by Federal News Service. Judge Sotomayor answered first-round questions from Senators John Cornyn, Benjamin L. Cardin, Tom Coburn, Sheldon Whitehouse, Amy Klobuchar, Edward E. Kaufman, Arlen Specter and Al Franken. Additional second-round questions were asked by Senators Jeff Sessions, Herb Kohl, Orrin G. Hatch, Russ Feingold, Charles E. Grassley  and Cardin. Senator Patrick J. Leahy also spoke during the hearing.

abstract: Judge Sonia Sotomayor said that no one in the White House asked about her views on abortion before her nomination.
snippet: Judge Sonia Sotomayor said that no one in the White House asked about her views on abortion before her nomination.
lead_paragraph: Closing Notes | 6:19 p.m. The session today seemed to allow Judge Sonia Sotomayor to loosen up a little more. At times, most predictably when she was questioned by Democrats, she talked without interruption for several minutes.
headline_main: Questioning of Sotomayor Turns to Abortion Issue

abstract: Senators begin asking their questions of Judge Sonia Sotomayor on the second day of her confirmation hearings for the Supreme Court. We’ll be updating throughout the day.
snippet: Senators begin asking their questions of Judge Sonia Sotomayor on the second day of her confirmation hearings for the Supreme Court. We’ll be updating throughout the day.
lead_paragraph: Tuesday’s session has ended. For Wednesday, several senators still have their first 30-minute question-and-answer encounters with the judge. Then, there will be a brief closed session while both sides discuss her F.B.I. background check, a routine event for nominees. Then the open hearings will resume, with senators getting second rounds of 20 minutes each.

abstract: Stay with us for updates throughout the day.
snippet: Stay with us for updates throughout the day.
lead_paragraph: A Few Closing Thoughts | 3:51 p.m. For the most part, Day One of the Sotomayor hearings unfolded uneventfully, as expected.

abstract: Our correspondents offer a guide to possible highlights and the weighty issues of the Senate judiciary’s hearings.
snippet: Our correspondents offer a guide to possible highlights and the weighty issues of the Senate judiciary’s hearings.
lead_paragraph: With the confirmation hearings for Judge Sonia Sotomayor before the Senate Judiciary Committee beginning at 10 a.m. today, several of our correspondents are offering up previews of what we may expect as the week unfolds. Many, if not all, are veterans when it comes to covering legal matters and Supreme Court confirmation hearings, and we’ve invited them to weigh in periodically as we live-blog the judiciary sessions once they commence this morning.
headline_main: The Sotomayor Hearings: What to Watch For
